      • subscribe

        public EZMQErrorCode subscribe(java.lang.String topic)
        Subscribe for event/messages on a particular topic. Note (1) Topic name should be as path format. For example: home/livingroom/ (2) Topic name can have letters [a-z, A-z], numerics [0-9] and special characters _ - . and / (3) Topic will be appended with forward slash [/] in case, if application has not appended it.
        Parameters:
        topic - Topic to be subscribed.
        Returns:
        EZMQErrorCode

      • subscribe

        public EZMQErrorCode subscribe(java.util.List<java.lang.String> topics)
        Subscribe for event/messages on given list of topics. On any of the topic in list, if it failed to subscribe events it will return EZMQ_ERROR/EZMQ_INVALID_TOPIC. Note: (1) Topic name should be as path format. For example: home/livingroom/ (2) Topic name can have letters [a-z, A-z], numerics [0-9] and special characters _ - . and / (3) Topic will be appended with forward slash [/] in case, if application has not appended it.
        Parameters:
        topics - List of topics to be subscribed.
        Returns:
        EZMQErrorCode

      • subscribe

        public EZMQErrorCode subscribe(java.lang.String ip,
                               int port,
                               java.lang.String topic)
        Subscribe for event/messages from given IP:Port on the given topic. Note (1) It will be using same Subscriber socket for connecting to given ip:port. (2) To unsubcribe use un-subscribe API with the same topic. (3) Topic name should be as path format. For example: home/livingroom/ (4) Topic name can have letters [a-z, A-z], numerics [0-9] and special characters _ - . and / (5) Topic will be appended with forward slash [/] in case, if application has not appended it.
        Parameters:
        ip - Target[Publisher] IP address.
        port - Target[Publisher] Port number.
        topic - Topic to be subscribed.
        Returns:
        EZMQErrorCode

      • unSubscribe

        EZMQErrorCode

      • unSubscribe

        public EZMQErrorCode unSubscribe(java.lang.String topic)
        Un-subscribe for a specific topic events. Note: (1) Topic name should be as path format. For example: home/livingroom/ (2) Topic name can have letters [a-z, A-z], numerics [0-9] and special characters _ - . and / (3) Topic will be appended with forward slash [/] in case, if application has not appended it.
        Parameters:
        topic - topic to be unsubscribed.
        Returns:
        EZMQErrorCode

      • unSubscribe

        public EZMQErrorCode unSubscribe(java.util.List<java.lang.String> topics)
        Un-subscribe for given list of topic events. On any of the topic in list, if it failed to unsubscribe events it will return EZMQ_ERROR/EZMQ_INVALID_TOPIC. Note: (1) Topic name should be as path format. For example: home/livingroom/ (2) Topic name can have letters [a-z, A-z], numerics [0-9] and special characters _ - . and / (3) Topic will be appended with forward slash [/] in case, if application has not appended it.
        Parameters:
        topics - List of topics to be unsubscribed.
        Returns:
        EZMQErrorCode
